{
  "stem": "22447.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the troops that came back, they had no clothes or nothing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Lost everything.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So were you closely associated with some of the returning troops?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And helped them out and--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, we had-- they said, well, you've been kitted out in the depot, so you've got to help out the ones that come back and share everything you've got with them until such times as supplies come through.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1940.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "June, 1940.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From there, we stayed in Cattistock, and then when everybody come back, when the Dunkirk affair was over, we were posted to the Isle of Wight because they said-- this was in June-- and they said, if the Germans are going to launch an invasion of England, they're going to go for the Isle of Wight first because that is the nearest place they can make a landing before going to the mainland.",
      "word_count": 73
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They won't go for the mainland, they'll go for the Isle of Wight first and build up and launch the invasion on the mainland in March.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "See, everything has to go to a timetable.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They took, the Germans took the Channel Islands but then over here they thought, well, it's-- it's no value, the Channel Islands, anyway.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's not going to win the war either way, so they just let them get away with it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the Isle of Wight was a key point, and we used to go there-- in the night, during the night, watch and see if there's an invasion coming or something, and in the morning we'd go back to the billets.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- but then they come round and they said, everybody should have a day off.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "What they call a day off, instead of going out every night until the morning, you helped the cook.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
